<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%">The Specialists Interview - <span class=bsmall>Sat 28 July 2001 14:30:08</span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2><a href="http://www.halflifeitalia.com/specialist/" class=colourise target=_blank>The Specialists</a> is a new total conversion for Half-Life. The mod will be set over a variety of different landscapes, including snow, urban and an airport, and will include a large number of weapons. It will also include the ability for players to peform a number of moves, such as dives or rolls. I interviewed John_Matrix, who is co-designer of the mod.<br><br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> Can you introduce yourself and describe what part you played in developing the mod?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> I'm John_Matrix, and I make the weapons models for the mod. I Also manage the forums, the website, and relations with the networks; then I'm co-desigher with Morfeo for this game.<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> Can you give a brief description of what The Specialists is about?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> TS is a total conversion for HalfLife that gives to players more moving freedom (dives, rolls, climbing/clinging abilities) really dangerous weapons (few shots and you're down), a great arsenal to choose in, and it's possible to add real life items on these weapons: silencers lasersights, flashlights, scopes and so on.<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How does your mod differ from other realism mods like Counter-Strike, Action Quake 2 or Front Line Force?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> The damages that you get from bullets are realistic (as i've already said) but the whole mod have an "open" gameplay: it's possible to behave in a "professional" way (large caliber weapons, kevlar protections and so on -this will affect agility but will increase the firepower-), and in a "spectacular way" (using small caliber guns -and this will let players be faster and difficult to be shooted-). I also specify that there aren't closed classes, you can decide all your equipment without any restrictions. And I think that i cannot say which kind of realism is between the great games you listed..... it's TS realism :D  <br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What was the main factor that made you decide to make this mod?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> We wanted a game made by ourselves with the features we like and in the way we like :) <br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> Who came up with the idea for this mod?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Both me and Morfeo.....we can say that he had in mind something different in the beginning...but I modified it! =)<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What kind of research is required for developing a realistic mod?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Kind of research.......I had the pleasure to know a friend who is an expert about firearms......and so =D.<br>The remaining part is.....in reality an headshot is deadful.....and so on :|<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> During development, did you get any ideas from watching movies or playing other games?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> we got many ideas......our main inspiration movies are John Woo's movies :D<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How long has this mod been in development?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> If i don't get wrong.......since... the end of the last year. Maybe December/January.<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> While making the mod, what difficulties have you experienced? How did you overcome these difficulties?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Since the beginning we've not got so many difficulties... cause Morfeo learned the C language very well and he soon learned also HL's engine!<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> Why did you decide to make your mod for Half-Life? Have you experienced any limitations by using the Half-Life engine? How much support (if any) have you received from Valve?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Until now we haven't got so many problems... and we've experienced few limitations. Better, nothing to be really noticed here (I can say that HL engine gives lots of limitations in terms of distance that can be seen...this is a great limitation). We've never requested Valve's help... maybe in future :)<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What sort of gameplay can people expect when playing The Specialists?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> As I already told, ppl must expect an open gameplay: the aim of the mod is team cooperation and in fact the mony earned is the one you get once you complete the objectives of the mission (killing will not bring you so much money). Winning the round will mean more cash for you and your teammates that allows to buy more weapons and accessories.<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How many weapons will be included in the initial release? What sort of weapons will be included?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> 7 Handguns, 6 Submachineguns, 3 Shotguns, 4 Assault rifles, 2 Light Support Mguns (LSW's) and 4 Sniper rifles. Then there will be almost all the real accessories for all these weapons (suppressors, scopes, lasersights/flashlights and so on...) Then some handgrenades, knives and you can also punch or kick your enemy! :D<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How many maps will included in the initial release?  What sort of settings will these maps be based on?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Until now we've got almost 7 levels. Not all of these are completely finished since we are testing the gameplay over them; for this they could be changed in some aspects. We've snow, city (a skycraper, a bad slum), airport (this taken from FACE OFF movie), cliffs (windward), and 3 more maps. <br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How large can people expect your initial release to be?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Mhh, i don't really know what about.....the latest version ( :) ) was near 45/50 megs.... i don't think that 45/50 megabytes are a problem for your modems :DDD<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> How much longer to do plan to keep developing The Specialists?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Hehe.... I can just say that we are finishing it :).<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What are you most proud of in The Specialists?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> I should say everything ( =D ) but I'm really proud of our weapons: they are tremendously dangerous, and I'm, also proud of the whole gameplay, that allows you to behave in the way you want (i do really like the "professional" way that I already mentioned :D)<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What advice would you give to anyone who is creating a mod?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> Just keep working for your game, don't mind ppl who don't understand what you are doing :).<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> What is your opinion of the mod community in general?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> I think that there are many good mods being played and developed for HalfLIfe.....this mean that the community is productive and people have great creativity. A mod is something special, something for which you spend a lot of time in developing it and also playing :DD<br> <br><span class=colourise>Question:</span> When can people expect the first public release of The Specialists?<br><span class=colourise>Answer:</span> As I already said..... we're finishing it :). Or better....... when is done! :P<br><br>Here are some exclusive screenshots from the slum map and include a new weapon (The Specialists fans will know which one it is). You can click on them to see an enlarged (1024x768) version.<br><br><center><a href="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0000.jpg" target=_blank><img border=0 src="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0000-small.jpg" align=middle></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0001.jpg" target=_blank><img border=0 src="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0001-small.jpg" align=middle></a><br><br><a href="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0002.jpg" target=_blank><img border=0 src="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0002-small.jpg" align=middle></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0003.jpg" target=_blank><img border=0 src="http://www.actionnation.com/images/specialist/slum0003-small.jpg" align=middle></a><br><br><span class=bold>ICE.M</span></td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
